## Runtime Validation

- Use {{VALIDATION_LIBRARY}} <!-- Zod / Yup / io-ts / Pydantic --> for runtime validation
- Define schemas alongside types, or generate types from schemas
- Validate all: API responses, form submissions, URL parameters, environment variables

```typescript
// Example: Zod schema + inferred type
const LoadSchema = z.object({
  id: z.string().uuid(),
  status: z.enum(['PENDING', 'ACTIVE', 'DELIVERED']),
  // ...
});
type Load = z.infer<typeof LoadSchema>;
```

---

## API Response Types

```typescript
// Standard envelope type
interface ApiResponse<T> {
  data: T;
  pagination: Pagination | null;
  error: ApiError | null;
}

// Usage: always type the inner data
const response = await api.get<ApiResponse<Load[]>>('/loads');
const loads = response.data.data; // correctly typed as Load[]
```

